TI - Mechanism of CDK activation revealed by the structure of a <p1  pair=2 >  <prot>  cyclinA </prot>  </p1>  - <p2  pair=2 >  <prot>  CDK2 </prot>  </p2>  complex .
PG - 313 - 20 AB - The crystal structure of the human <p1  pair=1 >  <p1  pair=3 >  <prot>  cyclinA </prot>  </p1>  </p1>  - <p2  pair=1 >  <prot>  cyclin - dependent kinase2 </prot>  </p2>  ( <p2  pair=3 >  <prot>  CDK2 </prot>  </p2>  ) - ATP complex has been determined at 2.3 A resolution .
CyclinA binds to one side of <prot>  CDK2 </prot>  ' s catalytic cleft , inducing large conformational changes in its PSTAIRE helix and T - loop .
These changes activate the kinase by realigning active site residues and relieving the steric blockade at the entrance of the catalytic cleft .
